HEADWORD: Imbursement
<hw>Im*burse"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
act of imbursing, or the state of being imbursed.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Money laid up in stock.</def>
